news.title: HDFC awaiting clearance for JV with Brookfield on real estate-dedicated ARC
news.para: HDFC is awaiting regulatory approval for the joint venture and aims to use it to provide last-mile funding and help resolve stuck projects. “We need such investors with deep pockets and who have long-term, patient capital,” said Deepak Parekh.

news.title: Greater Noida authority allows banks to also monitor escrow accounts
news.para: Until now, the authority has been setting up escrow accounts with private developers but did not allow participation of the banks that had provided funds to the developer for the project.

news.title: SC refuses to entertain fresh plea of Supertech to extend time to demolish twin towers
news.para: In October the top court had refused to modify its directive to demolish the twin 40-story towers in Noida for violation of norms and dismissed an application of Supertech Ltd seeking to save one tower and partially demolish 224 units in the other to conform with building by-laws.

news.title: Borrow-and-build model doesn't work any longer: Deepak Parekh, chairman, HDFC
news.para: ​"The most fatal financial mistakes always happen in good times simply because leverage is a double-edged sword. Leverage amplifies profits in good times but it kills during a downturn," Parekh

news.title: Oberoi Realty's profit up 94% to Rs 266.59 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: Oberoi Realty's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 768.52 crore in Q2 FY22, a growth of 136 per cent from Rs 325.28 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: JK Lakshmi Cement's profit dips 6% to Rs 87.29 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: JK Lakshmi Cement's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,226.38 crore in Q2 FY22, a growth of 7 per cent from Rs 1,149.60 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Shree Cements' net profit up 7% to Rs 563.94 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: Shree Cements' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 3,526.95 crore in Q2 FY22, a growth of from Rs 3,364.84 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Over 87,000 apply for PM-UDAY scheme in Delhi
news.para: The Pradhan Mantri - Unauthorized Colony in Delhi Awas Adhikar Yojna (PM-UDAY) scheme is being implemented by the Delhi Development Authority (DDA).

news.title: Embassy REIT's net operating income up 30% in Q2 FY22
news.para: The board of directors of Embassy Office Parks Management Services (EOPMSPL), manager to Embassy REIT declared a distribution of Rs 537 crore or Rs 5.66 per unit for Q2 FY22. Of this, Rs 4.52 per unit or 80% of distributions are tax-free for unitholders.

news.title: Dalmia Cement to set up Rs 577 crore plant in Bokaro
news.para: The cement maker had expressed commitment in this regard during the Jharkhand Industrial and Investment Promotion Policy (JIIPP) 2021 in New Delhi on August 28, launched by Chief Minister Hemant Soren.

news.title: Kaisa Group plans to sell property management unit, Hong Kong sites: Sources
news.para: Kaisa plans to sell its entire 67.18% stake in Kaisa Prosperity Holdings Ltd, a company with a market value of around HK$2.4 billion ($310 million), two sources said.

news.title: Land sharks encroach 40% land of Secunderabad cantonment board
news.para: An SCB engineering wing official said that a lack of funds has held them back from building compound walls along such areas and installing CCTV cameras.

news.title: China: Kaisa Group's shares fall on ratings downgrade
news.para: Kaisa's shares fell as much as 19.9% to an all-time low of HK$1.17 on Thursday afternoon, while its 11.25% April 2022 bond dropped more than 8 points to trade at less than 35% of its face value, according to data provider Duration Finance.

news.title: Evergrande makes coupon payment before Friday deadline: Sources
news.para: Evergrande, once China's top-selling developer, is reeling under more than $300 billion in liabilities, fuelling worries about the impact of its fate on the world's second-largest economy as well as on global markets.

news.title: CCP to sign leases with tenants of Panaji municipal market complex
news.para: The CCP has identified over 400 such tenants that were operating in the premises rent-free. PIL filed in the high court of Bombay at Goa in July 2017 had given the corporation one year to recover rent/licence fee arrears and initiate action against illegal occupants.
